          "id": "post-combinations-1",
          "title": "PCM vs PCB - Which combination should I choose?",
          "content": "I'm good at both Biology and Mathematics. How do I decide between PCM and PCB for Senior 5? What are the career prospects for each?",
          "authorId": "student-5",
          "authorName": "Rebecca Namuddu",
          "authorRole": "student",
          "createdAt": "2025-06-17T10:00:00Z",
          "updatedAt": "2025-06-17T10:00:00Z",
          "replies": [
            {
              "id": "reply-combinations-1-1",
              "content": "PCM opens doors to engineering, computer science, and pure sciences. PCB is ideal for medicine, pharmacy, and biological sciences. Consider your career interests and university requirements.",
              "authorId": "admin-1",
              "authorName": "Dr. Christine Namaganda",
              "authorRole": "administrator",
              "createdAt": "2025-06-17T11:30:00Z",
              "likes": 56,
              "isTeacherApproved": true
            },
            {
              "id": "reply-combinations-1-2",
              "content": "I chose PCB and it was perfect for my medical career path. Think about what you're passionate about - treating patients or building systems?",
              "authorId": "teacher-bio-adv",
              "authorName": "Dr. Peter Sserwanga",
              "authorRole": "teacher",
              "createdAt": "2025-06-17T12:15:00Z",
              "likes": 34
            }
          ],
